{
  "stem": "10768.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I immediately, with a doctor who is still alive-- he's in Binghamton, New York-- started to clean the room and putting together shelves.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "We should be able to take in patients.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "From United Nations world organization, a nurse-- a Belgian-born nurse, who was an extreme human being with a character that you don't have people like that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "She was probably-- she told me she was in the Belgian resistance, hating the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "She came and she provided us-- together with a doctor from England-- provided medication, basic medication, provided dressings, provided some instruments, a small sterilization where you autoclave the thing.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And we opened the clinic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And people from Mauthausen and from Ebensee and from the surrounding areas were coming to the clinic to get first aid or whatever need they-- whatever they needed.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "The, the type of, of-- if somebody needed, let's say, more bread, through the doctor, sometimes you got it, sometimes not.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Sometimes a little bit more milk for the children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "Until later on, beginning of 1946, a hospital opened in Bad Gastein.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "In Bad Gastein, the hospital, they took over an Austrian hospital, but it was predominantly for the local people but predominantly for, for the survivors.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And the hospital did an awful lot of good.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And the Jewish organization ORT has given there courses, nursing courses, in order to have Jewish nurses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And the course was very, very congested.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And every doctor was so devoted, even though they were not professors by-- they were not teachers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "But they gave an excellent program.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And after six months, a lot of girls-- for me, it was more upgrading course or a refreshing course.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "For others, it was a basic, basic course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "When I came to United States, the ORT, the certificate didn't mean anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
